<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,151,1148]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
Distribution (Map 
<number box="[412,428,980,1004]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="3.0">3</number>
). 
<taxonomicName box="[451,744,980,1004]" class="Insecta" family="Blastobasidae" genus="Barbaloba" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="meleagrisellae">
<emphasis box="[451,744,980,1004]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Barbaloba meleagrisellae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known from one collecting site on the western part of the Cordillera de Guanacaste in northwestern 
<collectingCountry box="[623,749,1015,1039]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,151,1148]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
Etymology. The specific epithet, 
<taxonomicName box="[575,740,1052,1076]" class="Insecta" family="Blastobasidae" genus="Barbaloba" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="meleagrisellae">
<emphasis box="[575,740,1052,1076]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">meleagrisellae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is derived from the Greek 
<taxonomicName box="[1048,1162,1052,1076]" class="Aves" family="Phasianidae" genus="Meleagris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Galliformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1048,1162,1052,1076]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Meleagris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the genus that includes the turkey, a bird in which males have a beardlike process on the anterior part of the breast, and refers to the setose lobelike process originating from the ventral part of the valva of the male genitalia.
</paragraph>
